        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Subheading text:</strong> Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy warned that <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/10/17/north-koreas-support-to-russia-is-first-step-to-world-war-zelenskyy-alleges" target="_blank"> North Korea's support for Russia</a> could be the first step toward World War III. He alleged that around 10,000 North Korean troops are currently being trained to join Russian forces in Ukraine, which he discussed during a meeting with EU leaders in Brussels.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Subheading text longer longer:</strong> In the Northern and Western Philippines, thousands of U.S. and Filipino troops have begun <a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/news/us-philippines-launch-war-games-china-taiwan-drills/" target="_blank">joint exercises</a>. This follows recent <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cvgd4yn45qlo" target="_blank">Chinese military drills</a>  around Taiwan and a <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/article/2024/aug/19/china-philippine-ships-crash-sabina-shoal-south-china-sea" target="_blank">collision</a> between a Chinese vessel and a Filipino patrol boat in the South China Sea. Taiwan reported a record <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2024/10/15/taiwan-reports-surrounded-by-153-chinese-military-aircraft-during-drills" target="_blank">153 Chinese military aircraft</a> near the island.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Subheading text longer:</strong> Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau accused India of making a severe mistake by <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/trudeau-says-india-violated-canadas-sovereignty/a-70518641" target="_blank">violating Canada's sovereignty</a>. He linked the Indian government's actions to the killing of a prominent <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/05/03/americas/canada-sikh-nijjar-assassination-suspects-intl-latam/index.html" target="_blank">Sikh separatist</a> and alleged a broader campaign of threats against Indian exiles. In response, Canada <a href="https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/timeline-india-canada-nijjar-usa-gurpatwant-pannun-khalistan-updates/article68755177.ece" target="_blank">expelled six senior Indian diplomats</a> amid rising tensions.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>Subheading:</strong> The U.S. has <a href="https://apnews.com/article/us-airstrikes-yemen-houthi-rebels-israel-hamas-war-99721f7f952d66d6da27e24dc3c189c3" target="_blank">launched airstrikes</a> targeting underground bunkers used by Yemen's Houthi rebels. Long-range B2 stealth bombers were employed against weapons storage sites in Houthi-controlled areas following <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-67614911" target="_blank">months of attacks</a> by the group on ships in the Red Sea corridor.</p>
